thread.title_full: Miramar football coach Senatus suspended one game - Sun Sentinel

author: Dave Brousseau
title: Miramar football coach Senatus suspended one game
text:
Tyler Huntley of Hallandale and Coconut Creek's Jhakari Harrison, arguably among the best quarterbacks in the state, will face off at Hallandale on Friday in a key District 16-5A matchup.
Huntley, who has thrown for 2,005 yards and 20 touchdowns in five games, had 515 yards and seven TDs last week against Miami Jackson. The Utah commit has 11 touchdowns in his last two games.
"He has put in so much work," Hallandale coach Dameon Jones said. "I'm not surprised how good he has been."
Harrison has thrown over 1,400 yards and has 21 TDs over five games. The Southern Illinois pledge has thrown for 12 touchdowns in his last two games.
"He has played well for us the past two years," Coconut Creek coach Kareem Reid said. "He knows what to do on the field."
Cobras to sit
Boyd Anderson WR Mike Nesbitt and QB Shabazz Telfort will not play against Coral Springs due to injuries suffered last week against Dillard.
Nesbitt suffered a head injury last in the second quarter and was taken to Broward Health Medical Center as a precaution. Cobras coach Eddie Brown said he would wait for Nesbitt to go though the required concussion protocol before allowing him to play.
Telfort, diagnosed with a sprained MCL in his right knee, is expected to return next week.
